eCrimex CCWG Data Stats

Arghya Mukherjee

06 January, 2021

eCrimex Data

eCrimex curates cryptocurrency wallet data from different sources which are involved in scams and different crimes. The data is available for the research community on request also we will make it available on our github.

In this document, we summarise the data that is collected periodically and updated everyday. The R code used to create the summary statistics are available on clicking code.

R Libraries used

#Required Libraries

suppressWarnings({
library(data.table)
library(ggplot2)
library(scales)
library(cowplot)
library(dplyr)
library(Polychrome)
library(kableExtra)})

Clean Data set

The timestamps provided by ecrimex are unix stamps. Hence, for visualization purposes, we convert the data into YYYY-MM-DD and then follow that up by creating a date variable with the first date of the the month (YYYY-MM-01). We then create a data frame with the count of reported date by month. 

ecrimex$timestamp <- as.Date(as.POSIXct(ecrimex$timestamp,origin="1970-01-01"))
ecrimex$modified <- as.Date(as.POSIXct(ecrimex$modified,origin="1970-01-01"))
ecrimex <- ecrimex[order(timestamp),]
ecrimex$year_mon <- format(ecrimex$timestamp,"%Y-%m-01")
ecrimex[,count_by_date:=.N,by=year_mon]
ecrimex_date <- ecrimex[,c(12,11)]
ecrimex_date <- unique(ecrimex_date)
ecrimex_date$year_mon <- as.Date(ecrimex_date$year_mon)

Summary Stats

These section of the document will show the summary of all the data that we have collected and follow that up with some plots.

Code for Time Series plot showing addresses reported by Month

# Code for Time Series plot showing addresses reported by Month
plot1 <- ggplot(ecrimex_date,aes(x=year_mon,y=count_by_date))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity")+theme_bw()+
  labs(x="Date",y="# Reported addresses")+
  ggtitle("Reported addresses by Month")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1,size=10))
plot_grid(plot1)

Code to fix upload date

ecrimex$year_mon_2 <- format(ecrimex$modified,"%Y-%m-01")
ecrimex[,count_by_date_2:=.N,by=year_mon_2]
ecrimex_date_2 <- ecrimex[,c(13,14)]
ecrimex_date_2 <- unique(ecrimex_date_2)
ecrimex_date_2 <- ecrimex_date_2[order(year_mon_2),]

Code for Time Series plot showing addresses posted by Month

# Code for Time Series plot showing addresses posted by Month
plot2 <- ggplot(ecrimex_date_2,aes(x=year_mon_2,y=count_by_date_2))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity")+theme_bw()+
  labs(x="Date",y="# Posted addresses")+
  ggtitle("Posted addresses by Month")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1,size=10))

plot_grid(plot2)

#coin pie
coin_pie <- ggplot(coin_count,aes(x="",y=coin_count,fill=factor(currency)))+
  geom_bar(width=1,stat = "identity")+
  theme(axis.line = element_blank(),plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5)) +
  labs(fill="class",x=NULL,y=NULL, title="Pie Chart of coin",caption="EcX: CCWG")+
  scale_fill_manual(values=as.vector(P80))+theme(legend.position="bottom")

coin_pie <- coin_pie + coord_polar(theta = "y",start=0)
